<h1 class="govuk-heading-l">Accessibility statement</h1>

<p class="govuk-body">This accessibility statement applies to the following website for Southwark Council’s digital NHS Health Check tool:</p>
<p class="govuk-body"><a class="govuk-link" href="@($"./{BuildQuery(IdQueryParam)}")" title="The Digital NHS Health Check">The Digital NHS Health Check</a>.</p>
<p class="govuk-body">Southwark Council owns the Digital NHS Health Check tool.</p>
<p class="govuk-body">We want as many people as possible to be able to use the website for the Digital NHS Health Check tool. For example, this means you should be able to:</p>
<ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
    <li>change colours, contrast levels and fonts</li>
    <li>zoom in up to 300% without the text spilling off the screen</li>
    <li>navigate most of the website using just a keyboard</li>
    <li>navigate most of the website using speech recognition software</li>
    <li>listen to most of the website using a screen reader (including the most recent versions of JAWS, NVDA and VoiceOver)</li>
</ul>
<p class="govuk-body">We’ve also made the website text simple to understand.</p>
<p class="govuk-body">You can <a rel="noreferrer noopener" target="_blank" class="govuk-link" href="https://mcmw.abilitynet.org.uk/" title="Access Ability Net for advice on making your device easier to use if you have a disability">access Ability Net for advice on making your device easier to use if you have a disability (opens in a new tab)</a>.</p>

<h2 class="govuk-heading-m">How accessible this website is</h2>
<p class="govuk-body">We have been working with the Digital Accessibility Centre (DAC) to improve the accessibility of the service. The digital service has had three DAC audits throughout its development; each audit carried out after additional technical and content changes were made to the digital tool. The latest audit was conducted by DAC in December 2021. Southwark Council have made all of the recommended changes in the report in an attempt to meet the highest standards (AAA success criteria of the Web Content Accessibility Guidelines 2.1 Content).</p>
<p class="govuk-body"><a rel="noreferrer noopener" target="_blank" class="govuk-link" href="https://www.w3.org/TR/WCAG21/" title="Access the Web Content Accessibility Guidelines (WCAG) 2.1 for guidelines on making content more accessible to a wider range of audiences">Access the Web Content Accessibility Guidelines (WCAG) 2.1 for guidelines on making content more accessible to a wider range of audiences (opens in a new tab)</a>.</p>
<p class="govuk-body">To the best of our knowledge, there are no known parts of this website that are not fully accessible. If you experience accessibility problems with the tool please contact <a class="govuk-link" href="mailto:takecare@southwark.gov.uk">takecare@southwark.gov.uk</a>.</p>

<h2 class="govuk-heading-m">Enforcement procedure</h2>
<p class="govuk-body">The Equality and Human Rights Commission (EHRC) is responsible for enforcing the Public Sector Bodies (Websites and Mobile Applications) (No. 2) Accessibility Regulations 2018 (the ‘accessibility regulations’). If you’re not happy with how we respond to your complaint, <a rel="noreferrer noopener" target="_blank" class="govuk-link" href="https://www.equalityadvisoryservice.com/" title="Contact the Equality Advisory and Support Service (EASS) for guidance">contact the Equality Advisory and Support Service (EASS) for guidance (opens in a new tab)</a>.</p>

<h2 class="govuk-heading-m">Technical information about this website’s accessibility</h2>
<p class="govuk-body">Southwark Council is committed to making the Digital NHS Health Check website accessible, in accordance with the Public Sector Bodies (Websites and Mobile Applications) (No. 2) Accessibility Regulations 2018.</p>

<h2 class="govuk-heading-m">Compliance status</h2>
<p class="govuk-body">Southwark Council have made all of the recommended changes in the report in an attempt to meet the highest standards (AAA success criteria of the Web Content Accessibility Guidelines 2.1 Content). <a rel="noreferrer noopener" target="_blank" class="govuk-link" href="https://www.w3.org/TR/WCAG21/" title="Access the Web Content Accessibility Guidelines (WCAG) 2.1 for guidelines on making content more accessible to a wider range of audiences">Access the Web Content Accessibility Guidelines (WCAG) 2.1 for guidelines on making content more accessible to a wider range of audiences (opens in a new tab)</a>.</p>
<p class="govuk-body">To the best of our knowledge, there are no known parts of this website that are not fully accessible and there are not any elements to the website that are non-compliant with AAA standards.</p>
<p class="govuk-body">If you experience accessibility problems with the tool please contact <a class="govuk-link" href="mailto:takecare@southwark.gov.uk">takecare@southwark.gov.uk</a>.</p>

