<h2 class="govuk-heading-m">Content that's not within the scope of the accessibility regulations</h2>

<h3 class="govuk-heading-s">Links to external web pages</h3>
<p class="govuk-body">Throughout the service, we provide links to external pages like the tool to find your GP Clinic through a postcode search, or for more detailed information on specific medical terms.</p>
<p class="govuk-body">At the end of the service, we provide links to external behaviour change support services.</p>
<p class="govuk-body">We are not able to influence the accessibility of those external pages.</p>
<p class="govuk-body">For more information on the digital NHS Health Check external web pages see our external links clause.</p>

<h2 class="govuk-heading-m">What we’re doing to improve accessibility</h2>
<p class="govuk-body">The website for the Digital NHS Health Check tool will be audited periodically by the Digital Accessibility Centre (DAC) to improve the accessibility of the service.</p>

<h2 class="govuk-heading-m">Feedback and contact information</h2>
<p class="govuk-body">We are always looking for ways to improve the accessibility of the Digital NHS Health Check tool website. Please contact <a class="govuk-link" href="mailto:takecare@southwark.gov.uk">takecare@southwark.gov.uk</a> if you have an accessibility query, accessibility issue, think we’re not meeting accessibility requirements or you have any positive feedback about the website's accessibility.</p>

<h2 class="govuk-heading-m">Preparation of this accessibility statement</h2>
<p class="govuk-body">This statement was prepared on 07 January 2022. It was last reviewed on 07 January 2022.</p>
<p class="govuk-body">This website was last tested internally in January 2022 by QMS. The last test carried out by the Digital Accessibility Centre (DAC) was in December 2021.</p>
<p class="govuk-body">Page last updated: 31 March 2022</p>

